        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Instead of removing the 6- (or 9-) level cap on lifetaps, modify it.</P><P>The best choice would be to make it 50%. So the level 12 necro group would cap at 18, still too low to kill sand giants. Whereas, the Warlock would be capped at 90, enough to land on any mob currently in game and likely through the next expansion.</P><P>Of course, that involves coding an entire calculation subroutine across a line of spells, so it's not likely to get added to the code. What might be possible is that the level-cap lifetap resist gets lifted at a certain level (54? 60?). Still keeps the lowbies down while allowing uber necros to act a little more uber.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
